 Title: Interference of Biocytin with Opioid-Evoked Hyperpolarization and Membrane Properties of Rat Spinal Substantia Gelatinosa Neurons

Summary:
This study investigates the effect of Biocytin, a membrane-permeant biotinylated dextran amine, on opioid-evoked hyperpolarization and membrane properties of rat spinal substantia gelatinosa (SG) neurons. The researchers recorded the membrane potential and input resistance of SG neurons in response to application of opioids (enkephalin and morphine) and Biocytin. They found that Biocytin interfered with opioid-evoked hyperpolarization, reducing the magnitude and duration of the hyperpolarization. Additionally, Biocytin decreased the input resistance of SG neurons.

