 Title: Pharmacokinetic Evaluation of the Digoxin-Amiodarone Interaction

Summary:
This study investigates the interaction between digoxin and amiodarone, two commonly used drugs in cardiology, focusing on their pharmacokinetics. The researchers found that amiodarone inhibits digoxin renal clearance, leading to increased digoxin levels in the body.

Key Findings:
1. Digoxin and amiodarone co-administration resulted in a significant increase in digoxin half-life (from 36.2 hours to 56.2 hours).
2. The renal clearance of digoxin was decreased by 42% when co-administered with amiodarone.
3. Amiodarone did not significantly affect digoxin absorption, distribution, or metabolism.

Cited Drugs:
1. Digoxin
2. Amiodarone

