  "Summary": 
  "This study investigated the effect of fluoxetine on the pharmacokinetics and QTc intervals of cisapride in healthy volunteers. The participants received a single oral dose of cisapride (2.2 mg/kg) alone or following 20 mg fluoxetine once daily for 5 days. The results showed that coadministration of fluoxetine increased the area under the curve (AUC) and maximum concentration (Cmax) of cisapride by 35% and 25%, respectively. The half-life of cisapride was also prolonged by approximately 30%. Regarding the QTc intervals, fluoxetine coadministration led to a significant increase in QTc interval prolongation compared to cisapride alone. The study concluded that fluoxetine may increase the risk of QTc interval prolongation when used concomitantly with cisapride."
}
